Casablanca,t2jBSAWCg5s,Ugzs07337x7eS2uriQ94AaABAg,,@garyi.1360,"The acting is great by all the cast.  Though what shines most to me is the writing.  The dialogue, as you say, is filled with those classic lines.  They are so perfect you can't believe there was ever any indecision for what the words should be.  And if you watch some of the documentaries about the production you can hear those stories.  One line that I like to point to is in the opening when a narrator sets the scene.  As he ends his part his hand off to the audience is perfect.  His words trail off, ""while others wait in Casablanca, and wait, and wait, and wait..."". How he says it, long drawn out, with almost boredom, and yet with intrigue is perfectly and exactly how we find the situation in Casablanca.  It's nearly Shakespearean in how well it involves and invites you to watch the tale as it begins.  And the sharp, wittiness and pacing in the story just keeps you enjoying it to the ending.  That as well is a perfect hand off for Rick and Louie's tales to set off into the future and with gladness and optimism.
Do watch it again as the writing just gets richer each time.",2026-05-03T07:10:30Z,2026-05-03T07:10:30Z,1,False,0.0,2026-05-14T02:01:06.868402
