Casablanca,t2jBSAWCg5s,UgwDvT8O74NycvorqNF4AaABAg.AWisrWH8lLpAWiup6jllFB,UgwDvT8O74NycvorqNF4AaABAg,@jamesmelton7637,"It seems like a good idea not to know anything about the story, but you need a really strong knowledge of history to understand all of this. At this time the US was not in the war. It was before Pearl Harbor was bombed. So the goal of Laszlo in going to America is not to escape the fight but to encourage American sentiment in favor of entering the war. The Germans would prefer not to have to fight America at the same time they are fighting Britain and Russia. This is why Rick saying he's for himself and sticks his neck out for no one makes him a proxy for America. The US like Rick has not always been neutral in world affairs, but at this crucial time it is.  

Much of the story is also metaphorical. When Rick is drunk asking what time is it in New York and he says they are asleep all over America, the metaphorical story is talking about the political climate. How late is it in the war, is it too late already, and why is America still asleep to the crisis instead of fighting? When finally Ilsa tells Rick she loves him and needs him to decide what's right for everyone, that's Europe reaching out saying it needs America to do what's right. That is precisely when Rick realizes he has an obligation to fight the Nazi regime, and we know that this is what America must realize too.

It's this three-part parallel story of love, politics, and adventure that makes this such a remarkable film story. The three concepts are perfectly intertwined. Then to tell this beautiful, elegant story we have a stunning visual language. Very nearly every cell of the movie can be taken and framed. Every shot is that beautiful. The acting of our four leads: Bogart, Bergman, Henreid, and Rains is unsurpassed and incredibly compelling. They all have great chemistry with Bogart and he with them. 

There is a reason it's in the running for best film ever. It's essentially perfect in every dimension. On top of everything the spiritual impact of joining human love with the desire for freedom cannot be outdone. You finish watching the movie feeling you are a better person.",2026-05-12T23:02:48Z,2026-05-12T23:15:03Z,0,True,,2026-05-14T02:01:07.382559
