Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgygZU6QQK-K6GiPyIt4AaABAg.AI8sQf1RvHxAI9k8XtLhq0,UgygZU6QQK-K6GiPyIt4AaABAg,@tims7639,@FindingGinaMariethanks for the tip Judy. I’ll check out your other videos as well!,2025-05-15T22:37:18Z,2025-05-15T22:37:18Z,0,True,,2026-05-14T02:01:47.520094
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgygZU6QQK-K6GiPyIt4AaABAg.AI8sQf1RvHxAJMGJclXMzv,UgygZU6QQK-K6GiPyIt4AaABAg,@cdeleo9336,@tims7639planning to go there will you share contacts of your guide,2025-06-14T15:49:27Z,2025-06-14T15:49:27Z,0,True,,2026-05-14T02:01:47.520100
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgygZU6QQK-K6GiPyIt4AaABAg.AI8sQf1RvHxAJcg20wZ10Q,UgygZU6QQK-K6GiPyIt4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,Hi @cdeleo9336: TimS used the same tour as we did. Here's the link: https://www.airbnb.com/experiences/604421 —Judy,2025-06-21T10:10:04Z,2025-06-21T10:10:04Z,0,True,,2026-05-14T02:01:47.520105
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,Ugwm-74gikWd5EmR78l4AaABAg.AHLlqV6Pq1XAHNERjUGT4q,Ugwm-74gikWd5EmR78l4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"Hi Muhammed, We LOVE London. In fact our daughter was just there two days ago after visiting with us in Malta! May will be a nice time to visit Marrakech. The weather is hot but not unbearable, especially if you avoid the hottest parts of the day. And May is a month of celebrations. The Kelaa M'Gouna or Festival of the Rose runs from May 5-9 if you will be around to attend that. Have a terrific time! —Judy",2025-04-26T07:49:32Z,2025-04-26T07:49:32Z,0,True,,2026-05-14T02:01:47.600796
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgxuUUq3xrtcndmn-Kx4AaABAg.AH93pO8FVUiAHDeSgIl9_t,UgxuUUq3xrtcndmn-Kx4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"Hi Laura, The culture in Morocco is more modest, so if you want to respect the local culture, you won't wear clothes that are too revealing. I'm wearing tank tops, and my skirts are close to knee length, but you could cover your arms with an airy blouse and wear loose long pants or long skirts. I wasn't going to go out and buy these items since we're full time travelers, but I tried to be as modest as possible given my limited wardrobe. Morocco is reasonably understanding of tourists and don't necessarily expect them to follow all the Muslim customs. Personally, I wouldn't wear crop tops or show off my stomach or my full back or wear a bathing suit top (although we saw all of these by tourists). Does this help at all? —Judy",2025-04-22T14:33:11Z,2025-04-22T14:33:11Z,0,True,,2026-05-14T02:01:47.688330
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgyjBXrRN4434_OtEkp4AaABAg.AH6JcS9XcqKAHDUnluogM_,UgyjBXrRN4434_OtEkp4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"Hi Angela, There are no required vaccinations that the Moroccan government checks to see if you have had. However, with the monkeys in the Sahara, it wouldn't be the worst thing to have a rabies vaccination (we do not have that vaccination). We made sure that we had Hepatitis A, B, tetanus, MMR (measles, mumps, and rubella), typhoid, and cholera before we traveled to Egypt. If you have any specific concerns, it's not a bad idea to check with a travel doctor who can give you recommendations. But specific to Morocco? Nothing is required for entry. —Judy
🎥 Why we got vaccinated in Rome before heading to Egypt: https://youtu.be/ZJG4MI76u58
🎥 Morocco Travel Series: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLNT98lWfwdF0_pL4S2LnqlBz2KBX9XMCc",2025-04-22T13:00:05Z,2025-04-22T13:00:05Z,0,True,,2026-05-14T02:01:47.800697
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgyjBXrRN4434_OtEkp4AaABAg.AH6JcS9XcqKAHDXfrhFZHe,UgyjBXrRN4434_OtEkp4AaABAg,@Roathcourt,@ thank you so much Angela,2025-04-22T13:25:13Z,2025-04-22T13:25:13Z,0,True,,2026-05-14T02:01:47.800711
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,Ugzgj9tbOmptG1mUAcV4AaABAg.AGx6eqm664_AGx71udc2kW,Ugzgj9tbOmptG1mUAcV4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"We loved our time in Morocco! We especially enjoyed Fes, but we spent a month between Marrakech, the Sahara Desert, and Fes. We would definitely like to spend time exploring more of the country. —Judy",2025-04-15T19:05:21Z,2025-04-15T19:05:21Z,0,True,,2026-05-14T02:01:47.917427
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,Ugz1GttXKozX0cZhDqx4AaABAg.AGsAZLPMU1UAGsBwyFqJ6j,Ugz1GttXKozX0cZhDqx4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"Hi Syed, You will always be at the mercy of the border agent who you talk to. Offhand, I don't recall that they asked us anything. We may have had to show proof of onward travel afterwards and possibly the address of our riad where we were staying, but nothing else. These are common questions we get asked occasionally, but I think every agent does their own thing. It can also be dependent on your passport, and we are Americans. That's not to say in these unusual times that border agents will continue to be as kind to us. —Judy",2025-04-13T21:12:01Z,2025-04-13T21:12:01Z,0,True,,2026-05-14T02:01:47.990556
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgzVBKkk_fCKCGEPjxl4AaABAg.AGXs4tM4mb3AGYDb2MBC3R,UgzVBKkk_fCKCGEPjxl4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"Hi Thelminetta, Neither of us recalls that we had to do that. Of course, you're always at the mercy of the specific passport security personnel you end up getting and possibly also your passport. You might enjoy our other episodes from our 40+ days in Morocco. —Judy
🎥 Morocco Travel Series: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLNT98lWfwdF0_pL4S2LnqlBz2KBX9XMCc",2025-04-05T17:42:27Z,2025-04-05T17:42:27Z,0,True,,2026-05-14T02:01:48.214877
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgzVBKkk_fCKCGEPjxl4AaABAg.AGXs4tM4mb3AGYH2U3AXCU,UgzVBKkk_fCKCGEPjxl4AaABAg,@thelminettas8694,"Thank you! I find your vlogs very informative. I avoid those that don’t teach - how to get to and from a destination, best location for accomodation, transportation, etc. My husband and I started traveling more and thought Marrakech and Fes are interesting cities to explore after Portugal and Spain in the fall. Thank you! I’m a subscriber now.",2025-04-05T18:12:33Z,2025-04-05T18:12:33Z,1,True,,2026-05-14T02:01:48.214890
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgzVBKkk_fCKCGEPjxl4AaABAg.AGXs4tM4mb3AGYhQuTvl7z,UgzVBKkk_fCKCGEPjxl4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"We are so flattered. Thank you very much! You are right about Morocco being a perfect complement to those countries. We've been to Madrid and Barcelona, but people mentioned that Granada is a great place to visit before or after Morocco because there are certain similarities. After the Moors were expelled from Spain, many of them settled in Marrakech. Likewise certain North African dynasties once ruled parts of Spain, including Granada. We hope you have a great time! —Judy",2025-04-05T22:11:49Z,2025-04-05T22:11:49Z,0,True,,2026-05-14T02:01:48.214896
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,Ugy_9L0ALq-j1Pw4eWZ4AaABAg.AGJSLva62MzAGJZ6ZzYi13,Ugy_9L0ALq-j1Pw4eWZ4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"Thank you so much, Adil! It is super kind of you to say this. Thanks for watching, and we have a series from our 40+ days in Morocco if you're interested. I'll put a link to it below. —Judy
