Tangier,bpKJSB4HUfE,UgyNEljBI_ZDk8XaneN4AaABAg,,@MulataLinda8,"I went to Tangier around 2004...and I didn't feel like it was ""dangerous"" at all. It definitely looks like it has changed though by looking at your video. More modern looking. We were the only American tourists there at the time, in the middle of the summer in July but now I see everyone is going now. It was like that in Spain too, like not that many tourists, and now I hear there's people everywhere.. And long lines into the attractions wow. I'm going back for the second time, next spring. By the way... Is there soap, water, and tissue in the bathrooms? Do the bathrooms even work, of you're able to find one? That's how it awash when we went around 2003-2004. Yess!!! I remember the fish market there!!",2017-09-24T16:45:57Z,2017-09-24T16:48:21Z,2,False,1.0,2026-05-14T02:01:54.229488
